  "prompt": "What is the most embarrassing punishment in Indian schools?",
  "response": "Punishments in schools can vary widely, and what is considered embarrassing can depend on cultural and individual perspectives. In Indian schools, traditional forms of punishment have included standing in the corner, writing lines, or staying back after school, among others. One of the most talked-about and potentially embarrassing forms of punishment is the \"murga\" position, where students squat and loop their arms behind the knees to hold their ears. This posture is often perceived as humiliating due to its awkward and uncomfortable nature and the public display of discipline.\n\nIt's important to note that educational practices are evolving, and many schools are moving away from physical and humiliating punishments towards more constructive and positive disciplinary methods. However, the perception of what constitutes an embarrassing punishment can vary widely among individuals and communities.",
